An 18-year-old student in Finland tragically killed eight people, including classmates and the headmistress, before taking his own life at Jokela High School.
The shooter, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, had posted videos online and subscribed to a page linked to a US youth planning a school massacre.
Flags flew at half-mast as Finland mourned the senseless loss.
The incident, rare in Finland, left the country in shock and disbelief.
Police confirmed the shooter acted alone, leaving behind a suicide note.
The victims, including school staff and students, were identified as the community tried to come to terms with the tragedy
